* does fractional money exist?
  No

* when (if ever) does rounding take place?
  Always that program require to show up the prices

* are costs and prices the same class of thing?
  No, costs are the money that producer spent in create some product, comercialize
  it, sell it, and the prices are the value you expect in return for each product.

* if a shelf of 100 cans is priced using “buy two, get one free”, how do you value
  the stock?
  The stock have to be valued with its maximum price, that is to say, it have to
  be assumpted that each product wont be selled as a part of the promotion, but
  individually. So the stock value is given by the cost of each can multiplied by
  the ammount of cans.
